The article discusses the Action Plan of the Global Initiative to Combat Nuclear Terrorism (GICNT) in support of strengthening global capacity to prevent, detect, deter, and respond to nuclear terrorism. The plan includes various actions such as capacity building, cooperation among partners, scenario-based discussions and exercises, coordination and collaboration with relevant international institutions, and dissemination of information and lessons learned. The GICNT aims to promote international cooperation, share expertise, and develop practical measures and resources to combat nuclear terrorist threats.